# Impact — Environment Variables

Copy to `apps/agency/.env.local` for local dev, or set in **Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables**.

## Required for production (Supabase persistence)

| Variable | Scope | Description |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` | Client + Server | Supabase project URL (`https://xxx.supabase.co`) |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Client + Server | Supabase anon/public key |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | **Server only** | Service role key — never expose to browser |

When `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` + `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` are set, Impact persists opportunities to Supabase `opportunity_records`.

Without service role key, falls back to local JSON file (not suitable for Vercel production).

## Recommended for production (access control)

| Variable | Scope | Description |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| `IMPACT_BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD` | Server | Enables HTTP Basic Auth on all routes. Use any username; password must match. |

Unset locally for friction-free dev. **Set on Vercel** before sharing the URL.

## Optional

| Variable | Scope | Description |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| `IMPACT_DATA_DIR` | Server | Override local JSON storage path (default: `apps/agency/data`) |
| `IMPACT_INGEST_SECRET` | **Server only** | Bearer token for `POST /api/signals/import` (Custom GPT / automation) |
| `IMPACT_SCOUT_SECRET` | **Server only** | Bearer token for `GET /api/scout/run` (Scheduled Scout cron) |

## Example `.env.local`

```bash
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJ...
IMPACT_BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD=choose-a-strong-password
IMPACT_INGEST_SECRET=choose-a-long-random-secret-for-gpt-actions
IMPACT_SCOUT_SECRET=choose-a-long-random-secret-for-scout-cron
```

## Security notes

- Never commit `.env.local` or service role keys to git
- Service role bypasses RLS — server-only until Supabase Auth is wired
- Basic auth is a temporary guard for internal MVP — replace with Supabase Auth in a later epic
